page.title: 18FLOWERS OF THE COTSWOLD WOOD
page.content: Branched Bur Reed (very few),Bitter sweet, Bramble, Bugle (lots _ carpets of it!),Cotton Thistle,Creeping Plume Thistle (lots in cattle fields),Common Sorrell,Common Wipplewort (lots), Common Ragwort, Campian (lots),Dog Rose,Elder,Fox Glove (two only), Forget_me_not,Giant Campanula,Giant Hairy Willow Herb (few),Honey Suckle, Lesser Speartwort,Lesser Birds Fool Trefoil,Meadow Cranesbill,Mullein (lots),Meadow Sweet,Oxe_eye Daisy,Purple Clover, Purple Tufted Vetch,Privet,Purple Loose Strife (lots) Ragged Robin, Rose Bay Willow Herb (Most common),Stinging Nettle, Speedwell,White Clover Welted Thistle, Yarrow. these were found on a walk through the woods from the Ridge following the logging paths to the far end of ashen plain woods.
